The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                               Good Morning
      Hello It's Wednesday , July 22 , 2009                    
	Eclipse    Watch solar eclipse at BITM and Science City through telescopic projection, pinhole cameras or solar goggles, from 5.30am. Open house quiz at BITM.    In Calcutta, the eclipse can be viewed from 5.28am to 7.30am. The maximum eclipse will occur at 6.26am, when 90.2 per cent of the sun  at 17 degree from the eastern horizon  will be covered.    Dont look at the sun directly while the eclipse is on. Use No. 14 welders glass or aluminised Mylar filter. You can also project the image of the sun on a clean surface through a pinhole camera.    BITM and Science City will show a simulation of the eclipse if the eclipse is not visible because of cloud cover.    
	School    Jacomun with The Telegraph at St James School, 9am.     
	Programme    Temptations with The Telegraph at Ice Skating Rink, 11am.     
	Golf    The Telegraph Cup Golf for Corporates 2009 at RCGC in association with Ballantines, 6.20am.     
	Art watch    Summer Show at CIMA Gallery, 2pm to 7pm.                                                                                                                                                                   
